headline: How Defense Stocks Could Find New Buyers if Dividends Go Away
summary: Investors in defense stocks will have to brace for volatility as domestic policy throws curveballs to the industry, wars continue, and the NATO alliance comes under strain.  On balance, higher growth should offset headwinds from the forced elimination of dividends, if that comes to pass.  Expectations for dividend cuts are typically a death knell for stocks.
